218308958.review:
recently finished control, saw the trailer for control resonant, and i remembered "man i bought alan wake a year back maybe? why did i not finish it?" well i guess now i remember why. 

this game confused me, because remedy made it, the same remedy that made max payne 1 and 2, made a third person shooter that to me personally, is just not fun. 

{STORY}
dont get me wrong, the story is great, i am very invested in it, the mystery of where alice is, who is the lady that hands the key to the house, and everything is very compelling to me, compelling enough that i forced myself to go through the game for a couple more hours. 

{GAMEPLAY}
sadly, this is it. the most important part of a game, and this part is sadly not fun. the shadowy enemies feels tanky, and it would be fine since they are also tanky in control, but here i need to aim a flashlight to said enemy to be able to shoot them, seems simple enough right? not really, the flashlight's battery is so small that aiming it for what feels like a few seconds drains it, then i have to add more batteries, then i have to reposition, etc etc. 

all of that would have been fine if movement in this game doesnt feel like utter garbage, which again, is very CONFUSING to me because remedy made MP1 and MP2, i guess one good thing about it is that Alan is a writer, not some cop, so it is natural that he moves like ♥♥♥♥ and also not that great at shooting? but again, this makes the experience just not fun. 

{RATING}
very sad to say this but this game is at best a 5/10 to me, the story is something special, something i want more of, but the gameplay makes me frustrated beyond belief, some may say skill issue or whatever, and maybe it is, but i have no problem completing MP1, MP2 and control, so im not fully sure. 

not recommended unless you really like the story.

